        "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
        "score": 1,
        "is_accepted": true,
        "last_activity_date": 1401893930,
        "creation_date": 1401893930,
        "body": "<p>Sharing mutable state should be avoided since it can cause error in your program. Especially if you are working in multi threaded environment. Also it can make you program much less readable. That's why communication throw modifying same state should be at least minimize.<\/p>\n\n<p>Coping collections and arrays as well as dates are common practice to make sure that you don't use in your class/thread same object that was provided from other object/thread.      <\/p>\n",
